COERCE_LABELING_PER_FILE

 [Previous Routine] [Next Routine] [List of Routines] 
 Coerce to the proper labeling.

 file_in. A string for the input file.
 file_out. A string for the output file.
 wanted_vars. An array for the wanted vars.
 log_file. A string for the log file to record missing vars.
 delete_unused_var=. A boolean, set to delete unused vars.
 delete_unwanted_var=. A boolean, set to delete unwanted vars.
 map_vars=. A dictionary with (old_vars, new_vars).
 unwanted_vars=. An array or a list of unwanted vars.

(See general/missions/rbsp/efw/rbsp_phasef/phasef_labeling/coerce_labeling_per_file.pro)

PHASEF_COERCE_L2_LABELING

 [Previous Routine] [Next Routine] [List of Routines] 
 Coerce the labeling of L2 data for the whole mission.

 probes. By default ['a','b']
 data_types=. By default ['e-spinfit-mgse','esvy_despun','vsvy-hires'].
 years=. By default is ['2012',...,'2019'].
 version=. By default 1 higher than the old CDF.
 test=. Set to do coersion for 2 files per year.
 in_root_dir=. The root directory for the input CDFs.
 out_root_dir=. The root directory for the output CDFs.
 delete_unused_var=. Set to remove empty data and unused support_data and metadata.
 delete_unwanted_var=. Set to remove unwanted data.

(See general/missions/rbsp/efw/rbsp_phasef/phasef_labeling/phasef_coerce_l2_labeling.pro)

PHASEF_MAKE_L2_VSVY_HIRES_V02_CDF

 [Previous Routine] [Next Routine] [List of Routines] 
 Make L2 vsvy-hires v02 data from v01.

 v01 CDFs are from rbsp_efw_make_l2_vsvy_hires.
 v01 CDFs have two formats. They are unified in v02.
 v02 CDFs have the same format (data, support_data, metadata).

(See general/missions/rbsp/efw/rbsp_phasef/phasef_labeling/phasef_make_l2_vsvy_hires_v02_cdf.pro)

RBSP_EFW_PHASEF_CHECK_CDF_CONSISTENCY

 [Previous Routine] [List of Routines] 
 Check if all CDFs in the given folder have the same variables.
 
 The root_dir should have CDFs saved in the following hiarachy: <root_dir>/YYYY/*.cdf

(See general/missions/rbsp/efw/rbsp_phasef/phasef_labeling/rbsp_efw_phasef_check_cdf_consistency.pro)
